alse,"issue":{"author":{"__typename":"User","login":"griesemer","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjg1Mjg5NzU="},"id":"I_kwDOAWBuf87lL_zw","number":77273,"locked":false,"databaseId":3845127408},"author":{"__typename":"User","login":"gopherbot","avatarUrl":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/8566911?u=be84be2341a1a28dc2ede61150f7ceaaf470b8ba\u0026v=4","profileUrl":"https://github.com/gopherbot","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjg1NjY5MTE=","name":"GopherBot"},"id":"IC_kwDOAWBuf87hxB4T","body":"Change https://go.dev/cl/738441 mentions this issue: `cmd/compile/internal/syntax: enable generic method syntax in parser`","bodyHTML":"\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003eChange \u003ca href=\"https://go.dev/cl/738441\" rel=\"nofollow\"\u003ehttps://go.dev/cl/738441\u003c/a\u003e mentions this issue: \u003ccode class=\"notranslate\"\u003ecmd/compile/internal/syntax: enable generic method syntax in parser\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","bodyVersion":"16db7840afe188d86205efc057485c7ab1e5f7badcb47567d7fc9ca3641ff40d","viewerCanUpdate":false,"url":"https://github.com/golang/go/issues/77273#issuecomment-3787726355","createdAt":"2026-01-23T01:39:27Z","authorAssociation":"CONTRIBUTOR","viewerCanDelete":false,"viewerCanMinimize":false,"viewerCanUnminimize":false,"viewerCanReport":false,"viewerCanReportToMaintainer":false,"viewerCanBlockFromOrg":false,"viewerCanUnblockFromOrg":false,"viewerCanPin":false,"viewerCanUnpin":false,"viaApp":null,"isHidden":false,"minimizedReason":null,"showSpammyBadge":false,"createdViaEmail":false,"authorToRepoOwnerSponsorship":null,"repository":{"id":"MDEwOlJlcG9zaXRvcnkyMzA5Njk1OQ==","name":"go","owner":{"__typename":"Organization","id":"MDEyOk9yZ2FuaXphdGlvbjQzMTQwOTI=","login":"golang","url":"https://github.com/golang"},"isPrivate":false,"slashCommandsEnabled":false,"nameWithOwner":"golang/go","databaseId":23096959},"__isComment":"IssueComment","viewerCanReadUserContentEdits":true,"lastEditedAt":null,"lastUserContentEdit":null,"pinnedBy":null,"__isReactable":"IssueComment","reactionGroups":[{"content":"THUMBS_UP","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}},{"content":"THUMBS_DOWN","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}},{"content":"LAUGH","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}},{"content":"HOORAY","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}},{"content":"CONFUSED","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}},{"content":"HEART","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}},{"content":"ROCKET","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}},{"content":"EYES","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}}],"__isNode":"IssueComment"},"cursor":"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpPPAAABm-iBnJgAqjM3ODc3MjYzNTU="},{"node":{"__typename":"CrossReferencedEvent","__isIssueTimelineItems":"CrossReferencedEvent","__isTimelineEvent":"CrossReferencedEvent","databaseId":4442071460,"createdAt":"2026-01-23T01:44:15Z","actor":{"__typename":"User","login":"griesemer","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjg1Mjg5NzU=","__isActor":"User","avatarUrl":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/8528975?s=64\u0026u=f805aea1bf2bea2dbd5c2aaed2cefcdab2205ef2\u0026v=4","profileResourcePath":"/griesemer","name":"Robert Griesemer"},"source":{"__typename":"Issue","__isNode":"Issue","id":"I_kwDOAWBuf87gAI3f"},"willCloseTarget":false,"referencedAt":"2026-01-23T01:44:14Z","innerSource":{"__typename":"Issue","__isReferencedSubject":"Issue","id":"I_kwDOAWBuf87gAI3f","issueTitleHTML":"spec: revisit presentation of syntax for index expressions","url":"https://github.com/golang/go/issues/76971","number":76971,"stateReason":"COMPLETED","repository":{"id":"MDEwOlJlcG9zaXRvcnkyMzA5Njk1OQ==","name":"go","isPrivate":false,"owner":{"__typename":"Organization","login":"golang","id":"MDEyOk9yZ2FuaXphdGlvbjQzMTQwOTI="}},"__isNode":"Issue"},"__isNode":"CrossReferencedEvent","id":"CRE_kwDOAWBuf88AAAABCMShpA"},"cursor":"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpPPAAABm-iGAZgCqjQ0NDIwNzE0NjA="},{"node":{"__typename":"IssueComment","__isIssueTimelineItems":"IssueComment","databaseId":3788416927,"viewerDidAuthor":false,"issue":{"author":{"__typename":"User","login":"griesemer","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjg1Mjg5NzU="},"id":"I_kwDOAWBuf87lL_zw","number":77273,"locked":false,"databaseId":3845127408},"author":{"__typename":"User","login":"Merovius","avatarUrl":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/720787?u=d0f2d4698a74da12816f76d92e6a6db9aa40d443\u0026v=4","profileUrl":"https://github.com/Merovius","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjcyMDc4Nw==","name":"Axel Wagner"},"id":"IC_kwDOAWBuf87hzqef","body":"I have no strong opinions on this proposal. I think it works and its benefits and downsides are mostly well-understood - whether it is a good addition thus comes down to subjective opinion. I just have one nit about the proposal text:\n\n\u003e if an interface syntactically can’t include a method with type parameters, then a generic concrete method naturally plays no role in satisfying that interface because there can’t be an interface method with matching type parameters.\n\nThis applies to the idea of having generic methods in interfaces, but it doesn't apply to the idea of generic methods implementing non-generic methods in interfaces (the `io.Reader` case mentioned).\n\nI agree that if we want generic methods, the proposed semantics are right¹, but I predict that this will become one of the most frequently asked questions related to generics. We should explicitly call that out in documentation.\n\nI also think people underestimate the importance of having generic methods in interfaces for the use cases they have in mind, so I think that most people who are currently requesting generic methods will shift to requesting getting generic methods in interfaces as well, but the proposal text already acknowledges that.\n\n[1] As to @mpx suggestion of explicitly instantiating methods: I don't like this idea either syntactically or semantically. Syntactically, functions without bodies are a very rare thing, so I don't think the analogy is helpful to most people. And replacing `[T any]` with `[byte]` as an indicator is too problematic because of the already confusing way this works in generic receivers: one of the most common questions we get is that people try to do this (have a generic `type X[T any] …` and then write a method `func (X[byte]) M()`) with the expectation that this will imply a [refined method constraint](https://github.com/golang/go/issues/65394#issuecomment-1933627587). To me, this indicates that people's expectation of what this syntax means would differ from what it would do.\n\nSemantically, it just doesn't seem to fit well into a language which uses structural typing for interfaces in general.","bodyHTML":"\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003eI have no strong opinions on this proposal. I think it works and its benefits and downsides are mostly well-understood - whether it is a good addition thus comes down to subjective opinion. I just have one nit about the proposal text:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003eif an interface syntactically can’t include a method with type parameters, then a generic concrete method naturally plays no role in satisfying that interface because there can’t be an interface method with matching type parameters.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003eThis applies to the idea of having generic methods in interfaces, but it doesn't apply to the idea of generic methods implementing non-generic methods in interfaces (the \u003ccode class=\"notranslate\"\u003eio.Reader\u003c/code\u003e case mentioned).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003eI agree that if we want generic methods, the proposed semantics are right¹, but I predict that this will become one of the most frequently asked questions related to generics. We should explicitly call that out in documentation.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003eI also think people underestimate the importance of having generic methods in interfaces for the use cases they have in mind, so I think that most people who are currently requesting generic methods will shift to requesting getting generic methods in interfaces as well, but the proposal text already acknowledges that.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003e[1] As to \u003ca class=\"user-mention notranslate\" data-hovercard-type=\"user\" data-hovercard-url=\"/users/mpx/hovercard\" data-octo-click=\"hovercard-link-click\" data-octo-dimensions=\"link_type:self\" href=\"https://github.com/mpx\"\u003e@mpx\u003c/a\u003e suggestion of explicitly instantiating methods: I don't like this idea either syntactically or semantically. Syntactically, functions without bodies are a very rare thing, so I don't think the analogy is helpful to most people. And replacing \u003ccode class=\"notranslate\"\u003e[T any]\u003c/code\u003e with \u003ccode class=\"notranslate\"\u003e[byte]\u003c/code\u003e as an indicator is too problematic because of the already confusing way this works in generic receivers: one of the most common questions we get is that people try to do this (have a generic \u003ccode class=\"notranslate\"\u003etype X[T any] …\u003c/code\u003e and then write a method \u003ccode class=\"notranslate\"\u003efunc (X[byte]) M()\u003c/code\u003e) with the expectation that this will imply a \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/golang/go/issues/65394#issuecomment-1933627587\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/golang/go/issues/65394/hovercard\"\u003erefined method constraint\u003c/a\u003e. To me, this indicates that people's expectation of what this syntax means would differ from what it would do.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003eSemantically, it just doesn't seem to fit well into a language which uses structural typing for interfaces in general.\u003c/p\u003e","bodyVersion":"b4498c131a5b9db41319e0096f4884076c38e1bcf2bb3029e366de402b5443ec","viewerCanUpdate":false,"url":"https://github.com/golang/go/issues/77273#issuecomment-3788416927","createdAt":"2026-01-23T05:45:49Z","authorAssociation":"CONTRIBUTOR","viewerCanDelete":false,"viewerCanMinimize":false,"viewerCanUnminimize":false,"viewerCanReport":false,"viewerCanReportToMaintainer":false,"viewerCanBlockFromOrg":false,"viewerCanUnblockFromOrg":false,"viewerCanPin":false,"viewerCanUnpin":false,"viaApp":null,"isHidden":false,"minimizedReason":null,"showSpammyBadge":false,"createdViaEmail":false,"authorToRepoOwnerSponsorship":null,"repository":{"id":"MDEwOlJlcG9zaXRvcnkyMzA5Njk1OQ==","name":"go","owner":{"__typename":"Organization","id":"MDEyOk9yZ2FuaXphdGlvbjQzMTQwOTI=","login":"golang","url":"https://github.com/golang"},"isPrivate":false,"slashCommandsEnabled":false,"nameWithOwner":"golang/go","databaseId":23096959},"__isComment":"IssueComment","viewerCanReadUserContentEdits":true,"lastEditedAt":null,"lastUserContentEdit":null,"pinnedBy":null,"__isReactable":"IssueComment","reactionGroups":[{"content":"THUMBS_UP","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":29,"nodes":[{"__typename":"User","login":"jub0bs","__isNode":"User","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjUyMzI1MTUw"},{"__typename":"User","login":"ClarkQAQ","__isNode":"User","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQwNzg1MTE4"},{"__typename":"User","login":"florianl","__isNode":"User","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjExMzI0OTQ="},{"__typename":"User","login":"stephenafamo","__isNode":"User","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEzNDcyNDU1"},{"__typename":"User","login":"ViniciusIth","__isNode":"User","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjc2NDEzNTA1"}]}},{"content":"THUMBS_DOWN","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":2,"nodes":[{"__typename":"User","login":"eustrainLee","__isNode":"User","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU1ODY5ODU3"},{"__typename":"User","login":"valyala","__isNode":"User","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI4MzQ0Mg=="}]}},{"content":"LAUGH","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}},{"content":"HOORAY","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}},{"content":"CONFUSED","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}},{"content":"HEART","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":1,"nodes":[{"__typename":"User","login":"johanbrandhorst","__isNode":"User","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjY2MDQxNTE="}]}},{"content":"ROCKET","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}},{"content":"EYES","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}}],"__isNode":"IssueComment"},"cursor":"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpPPAAABm-ljKsgAqjM3ODg0MTY5Mjc="},{"node":{"__typename":"CrossReferencedEvent","__isIssueTimelineItems":"CrossReferencedEvent","__isTimelineEvent":"CrossReferencedEvent","databaseId":4443382142,"createdAt":"2026-01-23T05:57:11Z","actor":{"__typename":"User","login":"ianlancetaylor","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMxOTQzMzM=","__isActor":"User","avatarUrl":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3194333?s=64\u0026v=4","profileResourcePath":"/ianlancetaylor","name":"Ian Lance Taylor"},"source":{"__typename":"Issue","__isNode":"Issue","id":"I_kwDOAWBuf849eVpl"},"willCloseTarget":false,"referencedAt":"2026-01-23T05:57:10Z","innerSource":{"__typename":"Issue","__isReferencedSubject":"Issue","id":"I_kwDOAWBuf849eVpl","issueTitleHTML":"proposal: spec: allow type parameters in methods","url":"https://github.com/golang/go/issues/49085","number":49085,"stateReason":"DUPLICATE","repository":{"id":"MDEwOlJlcG9zaXRvcnkyMzA5Njk1OQ==","name":"go","isPrivate":false,"owner":{"__typename":"Organization","login":"golang","id":"MDEyOk9yZ2FuaXphdGlvbjQzMTQwOTI="}},"__isNode":"Issue"},"__isNode":"CrossReferencedEvent","id":"CRE_kwDOAWBuf88AAAABCNihfg"},"cursor":"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpPPAAABm-ltktgCqjQ0NDMzODIxNDI="},{"node":{"__typename":"IssueComment","__isIssueTimelineItems":"IssueComment","databaseId":3790225216,"viewerDidAuthor":false,"issue":{"author":{"__typename":"User","login":"griesemer","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjg1Mjg5NzU="},"id":"I_kwDOAWBuf87lL_zw","number":77273,"locked":false,"databaseId":3845127408},"author":{"__typename":"User","login":"jub0bs","avatarUrl":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/52325150?u=9143754713c3d01df1448d846a04fef8989c9ed4\u0026v=4","profileUrl":"https://github.com/jub0bs","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjUyMzI1MTUw","name":null},"id":"IC_kwDOAWBuf87h6j9A","body":"This is exciting! I'm overall in favour of this proposal. How soon can we start playing with an implementation?\n\nHowever, I also have some concerns:\n\n1. How easy will this new subtlety (concrete methods can introduce type params, but interface methods cannot) to teach?\n2. Would this new functionality be released gradually, perhaps initially behind a GOEXPERIMENT flag? (I think it should.)\n4. There are proposals to allow tightening constraints in methods on generic types (e.g. https://github.com/golang/go/issues/65394 and https://github.com/golang/go/issues/64846). I believe this is what @Merovius calls _refined method constraints_. Such functionality is, IMO, also desirable. Is this proposal orthogonal enough as to leave the door open for refined method constraints further down the road? My impression is that the answer is \"yes\", but I'd like to hear it from @griesemer. 😇 ","bodyHTML":"\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003eThis is exciting! I'm overall in favour of this proposal. How soon can we start playing with an implementation?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003eHowever, I also have some concerns:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003col dir=\"auto\"\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eHow easy will this new subtlety (concrete methods can introduce type params, but interface methods cannot) to teach?\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWould this new functionality be released gradually, perhaps initially behind a GOEXPERIMENT flag? (I think it should.)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThere are proposals to allow tightening constraints in methods on generic types (e.g. \u003cspan class=\"reference\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"octicon octicon-issue-opened open mr-1\" title=\"Open\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M8 9.5a1.5 1.5 0 1 0 0-3 1.5 1.5 0 0 0 0 3Z\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M8 0a8 8 0 1 1 0 16A8 8 0 0 1 8 0ZM1.5 8a6.5 6.5 0 1 0 13 0 6.5 6.5 0 0 0-13 0Z\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003ca class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load title\" data-id=\"2109016738\" data-permission-text=\"Title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/golang/go/issues/65394\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/golang/go/issues/65394/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/golang/go/issues/65394\"\u003eproposal: spec: allow methods on generic structs which meet subset of type constraint\u003cspan class=\"issue-shorthand\"\u003e #65394\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e and \u003cspan class=\"reference\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"octicon octicon-issue-opened open mr-1\" title=\"Open\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M8 9.5a1.5 1.5 0 1 0 0-3 1.5 1.5 0 0 0 0 3Z\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M8 0a8 8 0 1 1 0 16A8 8 0 0 1 8 0ZM1.5 8a6.5 6.5 0 1 0 13 0 6.5 6.5 0 0 0-13 0Z\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003ca class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load title\" data-id=\"2054009481\" data-permission-text=\"Title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/golang/go/issues/64846\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/golang/go/issues/64846/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/golang/go/issues/64846\"\u003eproposal: spec: allow additional constraints on methods of generic types\u003cspan class=\"issue-shorthand\"\u003e #64846\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e). I believe this is what \u003ca class=\"user-mention notranslate\" data-hovercard-type=\"user\" data-hovercard-url=\"/users/Merovius/hovercard\" data-octo-click=\"hovercard-link-click\" data-octo-dimensions=\"link_type:self\" href=\"https://github.com/Merovius\"\u003e@Merovius\u003c/a\u003e calls \u003cem\u003erefined method constraints\u003c/em\u003e. Such functionality is, IMO, also desirable. Is this proposal orthogonal enough as to leave the door open for refined method constraints further down the road? My impression is that the answer is \"yes\", but I'd like to hear it from \u003ca class=\"user-mention notranslate\" data-hovercard-type=\"user\" data-hovercard-url=\"/users/griesemer/hovercard\" data-octo-click=\"hovercard-link-click\" data-octo-dimensions=\"link_type:self\" href=\"https://github.com/griesemer\"\u003e@griesemer\u003c/a\u003e. 😇\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e","bodyVersion":"645932ea63389735745e9bfc355d4638e36ab35f153d177d1a65afb0225edcef","viewerCanUpdate":false,"url":"https://github.com/golang/go/issues/77273#issuecomment-3790225216","createdAt":"2026-01-23T13:24:00Z","authorAssociation":"CONTRIBUTOR","viewerCanDelete":false,"viewerCanMinimize":false,"viewerCanUnminimize":false,"viewerCanReport":false,"viewerCanReportToMaintainer":false,"viewerCanBlockFromOrg":false,"viewerCanUnblockFromOrg":false,"viewerCanPin":false,"viewerCanUnpin":false,"viaApp":null,"isHidden":false,"minimizedReason":null,"showSpammyBadge":false,"createdViaEmail":false,"authorToRepoOwnerSponsorship":null,"repository":{"id":"MDEwOlJlcG9zaXRvcnkyMzA5Njk1OQ==","name":"go","owner":{"__typename":"Organization","id":"MDEyOk9yZ2FuaXphdGlvbjQzMTQwOTI=","login":"golang","url":"https://github.com/golang"},"isPrivate":false,"slashCommandsEnabled":false,"nameWithOwner":"golang/go","databaseId":23096959},"__isComment":"IssueComment","viewerCanReadUserContentEdits":true,"lastEditedAt":"2026-01-23T13:30:23Z","lastUserContentEdit":{"editor":{"__typename":"User","url":"https://github.com/jub0bs","login":"jub0bs","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjUyMzI1MTUw"},"id":"UCE_lALOAWBuf87h6j9AzpLeCkI"},"pinnedBy":null,"__isReactable":"IssueComment","reactionGroups":[{"content":"THUMBS_UP","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":1,"nodes":[{"__typename":"User","login":"Dessix","__isNode":"User","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQzNDk0Mg=="}]}},{"content":"THUMBS_DOWN","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}},{"content":"LAUGH","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}},{"content":"HOORAY","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}},{"content":"CONFUSED","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}},{"content":"HEART","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}},{"content":"ROCKET","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}},{"content":"EYES","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}}],"__isNode":"IssueComment"},"cursor":"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpPPAAABm-sGpYAAqjM3OTAyMjUyMTY="},{"node":{"__typename":"CrossReferencedEvent","__isIssueTimelineItems":"CrossReferencedEvent","__isTimelineEvent":"CrossReferencedEvent","databaseId":4446975487,"createdAt":"2026-01-23T14:55:03Z","actor":{"__typename":"User","login":"mfridman","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjYyNzgyNDQ=","__isActor":"User","avatarUrl":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/6278244?s=64\u0026u=0c2ce5bb2732022cd947e64cc7d4a0a481b22bf1\u0026v=4","profileResourcePath":"/mfridman","name":"Michael Fridman"},"source":{"__typename":"Issue","__isNode":"Issue","id":"I_kwDONhIxts7Q8Jf1"},"willCloseTarget":false,"referencedAt":"2026-01-23T14:55:02Z","innerSource":{"__typename":"Issue","__isReferencedSubject":"Issue","id":"I_kwDONhIxts7Q8Jf1","issueTitleHTML":"Moving \u003ccode\u003eGetFlag\u003c/code\u003e inside \u003ccode\u003eState\u003c/code\u003e?","url":"https://github.com/pressly/cli/issues/6","number":6,"stateReason":"REOPENED","repository":{"id":"R_kgDONhIxtg","name":"cli","isPrivate":false,"owner":{"__typename":"Organization","login":"pressly","id":"MDEyOk9yZ2FuaXphdGlvbjE4ODM1"}},"__isNode":"Issue"},"__isNode":"CrossReferencedEvent","id":"CRE_kwDONhIxts8AAAABCQ91_w"},"cursor":"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpPPAAABm-taAVgCqjQ0NDY5NzU0ODc="},{"node":{"__typename":"IssueComment","__isIssueTimelineItems":"IssueComment","databaseId":3791209509,"viewerDidAuthor":false,"issue":{"author":{"__typename":"User","login":"griesemer","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjg1Mjg5NzU="},"id":"I_kwDOAWBuf87lL_zw","number":77273,"locked":false,"databaseId":3845127408},"author":{"__typename":"User","login":"sudomateo","avatarUrl":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/24284972?u=565df4a6d38c57dc376e439099367e5b2d11fd96\u0026v=4","profileUrl":"https://github.com/sudomateo","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI0Mjg0OTcy","name":"Matthew Sanabria"},"id":"IC_kwDOAWBuf87h-UQl","body":"\u003e * How easy will this new subtlety (concrete methods can introduce type params, but interface methods cannot) to teach?\n\nI don't personally see this as a concern given that generic type parameters cannot be used today for either case. Those that need this new functionality will find it and understand the features and limitations and others will live without it as they do today. I do agree, though, that generic type parameters on interface methods will just become the next largest ask, but that was already covered earlier.\n\n\u003e Would this new functionality be released gradually, perhaps initially behind a GOEXPERIMENT flag? (I think it should.)\n\nI'm on the side of the fence that this functionality doesn't need a `GOEXPERIMENT` baking period, but I'm curious why you believe it does. Can you elaborate @jub0bs?","bodyHTML":"\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cul dir=\"auto\"\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eHow easy will this new subtlety (concrete methods can introduce type params, but interface methods cannot) to teach?\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003eI don't personally see this as a concern given that generic type parameters cannot be used today for either case. Those that need this new functionality will find it and understand the features and limitations and others will live without it as they do today. I do agree, though, that generic type parameters on interface methods will just become the next largest ask, but that was already covered earlier.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003eWould this new functionality be released gradually, perhaps initially behind a GOEXPERIMENT flag? (I think it should.)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003eI'm on the side of the fence that this functionality doesn't need a \u003ccode class=\"notranslate\"\u003eGOEXPERIMENT\u003c/code\u003e baking period, but I'm curious why you believe it does. Can you elaborate \u003ca class=\"user-mention notranslate\" data-hovercard-type=\"user\" data-hovercard-url=\"/users/jub0bs/hovercard\" data-octo-click=\"hovercard-link-click\" data-octo-dimensions=\"link_type:self\" href=\"https://github.com/jub0bs\"\u003e@jub0bs\u003c/a\u003e?\u003c/p\u003e","bodyVersion":"b317c70714bcee78f56878faf9d9b2ebfe47f2c21fb69b57bd7af4138deead9c","viewerCanUpdate":false,"url":"https://github.com/golang/go/issues/77273#issuecomment-3791209509","createdAt":"2026-01-23T16:48:15Z","authorAssociation":"NONE","viewerCanDelete":false,"viewerCanMinimize":false,"viewerCanUnminimize":false,"viewerCanReport":false,"viewerCanReportToMaintainer":false,"viewerCanBlockFromOrg":false,"viewerCanUnblockFromOrg":false,"viewerCanPin":false,"viewerCanUnpin":false,"viaApp":null,"isHidden":false,"minimizedReason":null,"showSpammyBadge":false,"createdViaEmail":false,"authorToRepoOwnerSponsorship":null,"repository":{"id":"MDEwOlJlcG9zaXRvcnkyMzA5Njk1OQ==","name":"go","owner":{"__typename":"Organization","id":"MDEyOk9yZ2FuaXphdGlvbjQzMTQwOTI=","login":"golang","url":"https://github.com/golang"},"isPrivate":false,"slashCommandsEnabled":false,"nameWithOwner":"golang/go","databaseId":23096959},"__isComment":"IssueComment","viewerCanReadUserContentEdits":true,"lastEditedAt":null,"lastUserContentEdit":null,"pinnedBy":null,"__isReactable":"IssueComment","reactionGroups":[{"content":"THUMBS_UP","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":8,"nodes":[{"__typename":"User","login":"adonovan","__isNode":"User","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU2NTgxNzU="},{"__typename":"User","login":"jonathansharman","__isNode":"User","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjkxMTk5NTI="},{"__typename":"User","login":"zzhaolei","__isNode":"User","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE3NTYxNzkz"},{"__typename":"User","login":"jimmyfrasche","__isNode":"User","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM3NTU1Mw=="},{"__typename":"User","login":"Throne3d","__isNode":"User","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU3NzEyOA=="}]}},{"content":"THUMBS_DOWN","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}},{"content":"LAUGH","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}},{"content":"HOORAY","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}},{"content":"CONFUSED","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}},{"content":"HEART","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}},{"content":"ROCKET","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}},{"content":"EYES","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}}],"__isNode":"IssueComment"},"cursor":"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpPPAAABm-vBpJgAqjM3OTEyMDk1MDk="},{"node":{"__typename":"IssueComment","__isIssueTimelineItems":"IssueComment","databaseId":3791377872,"viewerDidAuthor":false,"issue":{"author":{"__typename":"User","login":"griesemer","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjg1Mjg5NzU="},"id":"I_kwDOAWBuf87lL_zw","number":77273,"locked":false,"databaseId":3845127408},"author":{"__typename":"User","login":"kardianos","avatarUrl":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/755121?u=89bfd2a7740a0f8ac8111f45b63e4ecd51843c6f\u0026v=4","profileUrl":"https://github.com/kardianos","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjc1NTEyMQ==","name":"Daniel Theophanes"},"id":"IC_kwDOAWBuf87h-9XQ","body":"I appreciate that a generic method would not be used to satisfy an interface but would be treated (at least conceptually) as a namespaced generic function. This would meet a few of my needs pragmatically. Specifically, I make good use of SQL data table buffers and parameter fetching in some designs. I typically all something like `row.Get(\"ColumnName\").(int64)` . But if the backing type is actually an int32 it will panic (at times the differences can be subtle) or I need an enum outcome, it adds more complications by first asserting to an int64 and casting to the enum type. I would much prefer `row.Get[string](\"ColumnName\")` or `row.Get[enum.MyStatus](\"TheStatus\")`. I have a helper function today that does the same, but it tends to be under used because then I have to bring in another package or remember to use it. I don't need generic methods to implement interfaces. But for data access, this will be extremely useful.\n\nThank you.","bodyHTML":"\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003eI appreciate that a generic method would not be used to satisfy an interface but would be treated (at least conceptually) as a namespaced generic function. This would meet a few of my needs pragmatically. Specifically, I make good use of SQL data table buffers and parameter fetching in some designs. I typically all something like \u003ccode class=\"notranslate\"\u003erow.Get(\"ColumnName\").(int64)\u003c/code\u003e . But if the backing type is actually an int32 it will panic (at times the differences can be subtle) or I need an enum outcome, it adds more complications by first asserting to an int64 and casting to the enum type. I would much prefer \u003ccode class=\"notranslate\"\u003erow.Get[string](\"ColumnName\")\u003c/code\u003e or \u003ccode class=\"notranslate\"\u003erow.Get[enum.MyStatus](\"TheStatus\")\u003c/code\u003e. I have a helper function today that does the same, but it tends to be under used because then I have to bring in another package or remember to use it. I don't need generic methods to implement interfaces. But for data access, this will be extremely useful.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003eThank you.\u003c/p\u003e","bodyVersion":"13136b56fc7a4a6694b2331e150ab3fdcf37266020cf4035f7c1cbd776724f4c","viewerCanUpdate":false,"url":"https://github.com/golang/go/issues/77273#issuecomment-3791377872","createdAt":"2026-01-23T17:22:40Z","authorAssociation":"CONTRIBUTOR","viewerCanDelete":false,"viewerCanMinimize":false,"viewerCanUnminimize":false,"viewerCanReport":false,"viewerCanReportToMaintainer":false,"viewerCanBlockFromOrg":false,"viewerCanUnblockFromOrg":false,"viewerCanPin":false,"viewerCanUnpin":false,"viaApp":null,"isHidden":false,"minimizedReason":null,"showSpammyBadge":false,"createdViaEmail":false,"authorToRepoOwnerSponsorship":null,"repository":{"id":"MDEwOlJlcG9zaXRvcnkyMzA5Njk1OQ==","name":"go","owner":{"__typename":"Organization","id":"MDEyOk9yZ2FuaXphdGlvbjQzMTQwOTI=","login":"golang","url":"https://github.com/golang"},"isPrivate":false,"slashCommandsEnabled":false,"nameWithOwner":"golang/go","databaseId":23096959},"__isComment":"IssueComment","viewerCanReadUserContentEdits":true,"lastEditedAt":null,"lastUserContentEdit":null,"pinnedBy":null,"__isReactable":"IssueComment","reactionGroups":[{"content":"THUMBS_UP","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":13,"nodes":[{"__typename":"User","login":"ViniciusIth","__isNode":"User","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjc2NDEzNTA1"},{"__typename":"User","login":"DeedleFake","__isNode":"User","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMyNjc1MA=="},{"__typename":"User","login":"doggedOwl","__isNode":"User","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE2Nzc3MTgx"},{"__typename":"User","login":"jonathansharman","__isNode":"User","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjkxMTk5NTI="},{"__typename":"User","login":"aarongable","__isNode":"User","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI0NzQ5MjY="}]}},{"content":"THUMBS_DOWN","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}},{"content":"LAUGH","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}},{"content":"HOORAY","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}},{"content":"CONFUSED","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}},{"content":"HEART","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}},{"content":"ROCKET","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}},{"content":"EYES","viewerHasReacted":false,"reactors":{"totalCount":0,"nodes":[]}}],"__isNode":"IssueComment"},"cursor":"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpPPAAABm-vhJ